textsrv.key: Assembly data is stored in a BOM view Revision. When double-clicking on a BOM View, its assembly is opened in the Structure Manager application.
A BOM View Revision stores the single-level assembly structure of an Item Revision.
BOM View Revisions are only meaningful in the context of the Item Revisions for which they are created.
Double-clicking on a BOM View Revision opens that particular revision BOM in the Structure Manager application.
By default, the command does not allow a change to the type of the Item.
The "Contents" section below only shows Envelope objects.
The "Contents" section below only shows Items and Folders.
This tab shows the datasets (files) that are attached to this revision.
Deletion of a Folder does not delete its contents.
Use the "Edit" button to modify the Item Revision Master Form Attributes displayed in the table.
Files can be imported from Windows by dragging and dropping them on a revision.
The Inbox contains three folders: Tasks to Perform, Tasks to Track and Schedule Tasks.
Use the Inbox to perform Workflow jobs, Schedule Tasks and view additional information.
If the Inbox contains unviewed tasks, its name is highlighted and the number of unviewed tasks is displayed.

The "Item Save As" command only allows to save an Item to a different Item ID.
The "Item Revision Save As" command allows to save an Item Revision to a different Item ID.
This tab shows components and/or sub-assemblies of the selected assembly.

Use the "Edit" button to modify the standard Revision Master Form Attributes displayed in the table.

Any assigned task appears in the "Tasks to Perform" folder. Once the completion criteria of a task are met (for example, the required quorum of approvals for a perform-signoffs task have been granted), the task is completed and is removed from the folder.
Use the links below to open objects from the list.

If you initiate a process but are not responsible for the currently active task, Teamcenter places the task in the "Tasks to Track" folder. When the completion criteria of the task are met, it is removed from the folder.
Tasks are color-coded: black = The task has no duration. green = The task duration has not been exceeded. red = The task duration has been exceeded.
Schedule Tasks are normally assigned from a schedule. You can also take responsibility for a task.
The Worklist tree includes the Inbox.
The Worklist tree can also include the inbox of users for whom you are acting as surrogate.
This tab shows the workflow processes referencing the current object.
Impacted Items are the old revision or version of content (Part, Design Component, Part Usage, Document, Item revision, etc.) being revised or replaced as part of the change.
Problem Items are the contents (Part, Design Component, Part Usage, Document, Item revision etc.) causing the change.
Reference Items and Files are not modified or released by the Change.
Solution Items are the new revisions or versions of content (Part, Design Component, Part Usage, Document, Item revision, etc.) that are to be released by this change.
Vendor and Commercial Parts are to be attached at the Vendor Item level, not at the Vendor Revision level.
Locations and Contacts are attached at the Vendor Item level, not this Vendor Revision.
A Vendor Part cannot be attached directly to a Commercial Part. Create and attach a Vendor Part in the section above.
